cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper is primarily focused on predicting cyber attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of unconventional signals and Bayesian networks for prediction suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The use of different data sources and time granularities also suggests the involvement of data science (cs.DS) and possibly social networks (cs.SI) as a source of data.
